node.text: Here is a tardigrade walking in slow motion. Seeing how the individual 8 waterbear legs move is an interesting look at their wiggle. Note the tiny claws on each foot. These micro animals are currently walking on both the International Space Station and in an undersea habitat. Magnified 200x brightfield under iPhone slowmo. #waterbear #waterbears #tardigrade #microbe #microbes #microbiology #science #slowmo #slowmotion #thick #bear #nature #wildlife #walk #pondlife #freshwater

node.text: Here is a Tardigrade walking across the slide in real time. This freshwater species, Hypsibius exemplaris, is also currently walking (or floating) on the ISS in space- from this same culture. The green within is some algae it has ingested. Note the two dark eyes and 8 legs. #waterbear #tardigrade #bear #microbe #microbiology #ecology #science #iss #space #walking #microscopy #wildlife #animal #cute #algae #freshwater #pondlife

node.text: A tardigrade walking over a small obstacle. This water bear is a multicellular animal that is only 200 microns long. It’s brothers and sisters are currently orbiting the planet on the International Space Station. It’s two black eyes are clearly seen here, as well as the little claws on each of the 8 legs. Freshwater from the culture sent to ISS magnified 100X DIC #tardigrade #waterbear #iss #space #nasa #microbe #microbiology #animals #wildlife #freshwater #pondlife #ecology #cute #science #creature

node.text: A tardigrade wiggles out of its old skin. The protective cuticle will not go to waste, as 3 eggs have been laid within it. This freshwater water bear species is Hypsibius exemplaris and from the exact same culture which was launched to space last month and is now aboard the ISS. The smaller dots are protists. Viewed with 100x DIC #tardigrade #waterbear #microbe #animal #wildlife #eggs #space #alien #cute #microbe #microbiology #science #pondlife #freshwater #space #iss #odd

node.text: Most microbes including amoebas are safe and beneficial. So is this one, except in rare circumstances where it causes a fatal infection in humans in which it eats the brain. Naegleria fowleri is common in warm fresh waters, but the infection is accidental and very rare. This cell is about 20 microns across and moves with pseudopods. Viewed under 400x phase contrast microscopy sped 6x real time. #amoeba #pathogen #disease #microbe #microbes #science #microbiology #pondlife #florida #freshwater #protist #cellbiology #cell #wildlife #creepy

node.text: Here are three Naegleria fowleri “brain eating amoeba” cells. They are called this because that is exactly what they do. Although common and natural in freshwater ecosystems, under rare circumstances they enter the human body where they feed on the brain causing death. These small single cells are shown in time lapse. For more info on this topic check out the latest video from @bravewilderness where my good friend @realmarkvins and I hunt these in the wild! Viewed with 200x phase contrast and sped 6x real time from a culture #amoeba #braineater #bravewilderness #protist #disease #microbe #timelapse #science #microbiology #brain #pathogen #cell #amoebas #infection #freshwater #florida #pondlife #foodchain

node.text: Here is an amazing larval creature. This is the queen conch, Aliger gigas. They only hatch at 9pm, so this one was ~14 hours old. It is around 300 microns in length, and uses its ciliated mouth parts to collect micro algae. Special thanks to my great colleague @queenconch2020 for bringing this sample into the lab! Observing these creatures was a rare opportunity. #conch #shellfish #aquaculture #larvae #marinebiology #ocean #microbe #microbiology #algae #science #queenconch #mollusk #cute #hboi #shell #sea

node.text: Last weekend I conducted an Aquanaut mission 9 meters down in an undersea habitat. We spent over 25 consecutive hours underwater on this saturation dive. I examined the microbial mats around the habitat, which required a compact and powerful microscope. Luckily I had the Em1 which performed great under pressure. Taking micrographs on the sea floor was an amazing experience, thanks to @emmicroscope for sponsoring mission # 4534. #em1microscope #undersea #research #saturationdiving #microscope #microscopy #science #marinebiology #sealife #ocean #microbiology #habitat #aquatic #seafloor #ootd #exploration #oceanview #florida #scientist #seafloor

node.text: This is a Portuguese man o’ war tentacle under the microscope. Physalia physalia is a siphonophore with a powerful sting. Why? Because they have tentacles packed with these painful stinging cells. Each small circle here is a single nematocyst cell, look closely to see a coiled up harpoon inside ready to inject venom. Collected with @realmarkvins on a Florida beach for the latest @bravewilderness video. Magnified with 200X phase contrast microscopy. #bravewilderness #manowar #jellyfish #venom #sting #venom #microscopy #microbiology #micro #science #florida #cell #marinebiology #ocean #sealife #animal #venemous #biology

node.text: Here are two rotifers filter feeding in time lapse. There is a lot of bacteria in this sample, which are the small wiggling lines in the background, revealed with phase contrast. These two micro animals are anchored into some detritus, and seem happy with their spot. Video is 6x real time and 200x magnified, from a freshwater culture.  #rotifer #bacteria #feeding #microbe #microbes #rotifers #microbiology #timelapse #animals #wildlife #nature #odd #pondlife #ecology #biodiversity #freshwater #ecosystem #alien
